Section 5 Exercise Notes

you'll be asked to "Make all inputs have a 3px red border", this should say "Make all inputs (except the checkboxes) have a 3px red border". Checkbox elements cannot be styled directly. If you're wondering how to style them, you can checkout https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4148499/how-to-style-a-checkbox-using-css.

Meanwhile, around the 1 minute and 40 second mark Colt mistakenly uses the CSS color property, but he should have used either the background or background-color property. He makes the correction in the solution video.